Define a function to get the number of compute devices
The first function we‚Äôll define will create a list of available device names and return the number of devices accessible by OpenVINO. We‚Äôll use this information to select which device to use to perform inference from the Unity application. There might be an option named GNA (Gaussian & Neural Accelerator). GNA is a highly specialized neural coprocessor for tasks like noise cancellation. We‚Äôll exclude it from the list of devices presented to the end user.

ov::Core::get_available_devices(): Returns devices available for inference


/// &lt;summary&gt;
/// Get the number of available compute devices
/// &lt;/summary&gt;
/// &lt;returns&gt;The number of available devices&lt;/returns&gt;
DLLExport int GetDeviceCount() 
{
    // Reset list of available compute devices
    available_devices.clear();

    // Populate list of available compute devices
    for (std::string device : core.get_available_devices()) {
        // Skip GNA device
        if (device.find("GNA") == std::string::npos) {
            available_devices.push_back(device);
        }
    }
    // Return the number of available compute devices
    return available_devices.size();
}
