It also includes a field to control how often to unload memory assets when using Barracuda‚Äôs Pixel Shader backend. The Pixel Shader backend enables GPU inference on platforms that don‚Äôt support Compute Shaders. However, there seems to be a bug in the current version of Barracuda, which does not release unused assets when using this backend. Left unchecked, this can fill up both system and GPU memory. We can address this by manually freeing memory. Doing that every frame can hurt performance, so we‚Äôll only do it at set intervals.
[Header("Settings")]
[Tooltip("Interval (in frames) for unloading unused assets with Pixel Shader backend")]
[SerializeField] private int pixelShaderUnloadInterval = 100;


